                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16991213-13-off61 t16991213-13-cd62"></join> last. The Prosecutor said, that he was standing at his Door at Kensington; the Prisoner came to him, and asked him, if the Man lived there that lived there formerly, with that he replied yes; then the Prisoner told him, that he came out of Pembrook shire, from his Sister-in-Law, and had a Token for him, a Vessel of Ale, a Barrel of Pickled Oysters, and a Piece of Flannen; with that he desired him to walk in, which he did, and treated him with what was in the House; but it happened that some Granadeers were quarrelling at the Door, and he went to see what was the matter: in the mean time the Prisoner slipt into the Seller and took the Goods, and went his way, but being pursued, he was taken in Hide Park, with the Goods upon him: He had but little to say for himself, and could not call any to his Reputation; the Jury found him <rs id="t16991213-13-verdict63" type="verdictDescription">
